{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἄχῠρον</b> [ᾰ], τό, <br /> mostly in <i>plural</i> ἄχυρα, <b>chaff, bran, husks</b> left after threshing or grinding, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.72, 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 161, 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 226.2, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 18.1; ἐν τοῖς ἀ. κυλινδομένην 5th c.BC: Hermippus Comicus 47: _sing._, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 8.4.1, NT.Matt.3.12, etc.: proverbial, ὄνος εἰς ἄχυρα\">NT+5th c.BC+</a>] 'pig in clover', of unexpected good fortune, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 188, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 76: _metaphorically_, ἄχυρα τῶν ἀστῶν, of μέτοικοι, [prev. author] “Ach.” 508\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἄχυρα ἀπὸ τοῦ τοίχου ἀποσπᾶν, of dying persons, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “προγνωστικόν” 4. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> in <i>plural</i>, ἄ. χρυσοχοϊκά <b>slag</b> from gold-smelting, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PHolm.” 5.7.\">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G0892","accentedUnicode":"ἄχυρον","shortDef":"chaff","mediumDef":"<b>chaff, straw broken up</b>, by treading out the grain, <ref='Mat.3.12'>Mt. 3:12</ref>; <ref='Luk.3.17'>Lk. 3:17</ref>*","stepGloss":"chaff","stepTransliteration":"achuron","count":2,"_es_Definition":"paja (de grano)","_zh_tw_Definition":"穀殼, 糠 (太 3:12; 路 3:17)","_zh_Definition":"谷壳, 糠 (太 3:12; 路 3:17)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"vỏ trấu","_zh_tw_Gloss":"糠","_es_Gloss":"paja","_zh_Gloss":"糠"}]}